    <PrimAttribute name="manual" id="02025c7e-54d0-47b3-8d62-92118c16e2e6">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Boolean"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>As of 8.4.2.090 when (break) bulk cargo is split and has weight or volume-based invoice lines, these lines are also split to go with the new cargo created.
A new invoice line is created with a proportion of the quantity and hence value based on the split weight or volume.
The existing line is also scaled to match by the weight/volume.

Both lines are made manual but with myTransactionTI still set, both to show where the lines came from, and to distinguish these lines from regular lines
and 'normal' manual lines.
If the cargo is split again, the lines are also split.  If the cargo is merged, the lines are simply moved to the target cargo but not consolidated as such.

If there are cash payments, these are also split along with an associated CM_ProformaDetails.

Both quantity and value are scaled by the volume/weight difference.

This was done for TFS 1990 to keep cash payments with split and merged cargo so it can be released without an incorrect 'unpaid' error message, buut the invoice line processing
is done whether cash is enabled or not.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
